WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.011 --> 00:00:15.015
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

2
00:00:18.393 --> 00:00:19.894
Are you suggesting

3
00:00:20.729 --> 00:00:22.439
that I should fabricate the truth?

4
00:00:22.522 --> 00:00:25.150
-What? Where'd you get that?
-We don't have evidence.

5
00:00:25.650 --> 00:00:28.570
You want me to pretend
I saw Mr. Kim kill Min-hui.

6
00:00:29.070 --> 00:00:31.614
I wasn't at the hospital.
I didn't see anyone or observe--

7
00:00:31.698 --> 00:00:33.199
Enough! Just shut your mouth!

8
00:00:35.076 --> 00:00:37.704
You weren't at the hospital.
but you know what happened there.

9
00:00:38.538 --> 00:00:41.124
It's not lying if you know the truth.

10
00:00:41.207 --> 00:00:44.711
And the truth is.
Su-hun went to meet the letter-writer.

11
00:00:44.794 --> 00:00:46.629
He basically admitted
to committing the crime

12
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:49.716
when he showed up
to discuss the security footage.

13
00:00:49.799 --> 00:00:50.884
That's what counts.

14
00:00:50.967 --> 00:00:53.762
And you were at the park
to witness that yourself. Lee Kang!

15
00:00:58.099 --> 00:01:00.643
Hey. Why are you so quiet?

16
00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:06.941
Because I wouldn't be writing
about my own experience.

17
00:01:07.025 --> 00:01:09.486
This would be the opposite
of what you've been telling me.

18
00:01:09.569 --> 00:01:13.198
All this time you've been teaching me.
you said a writer must be objective.

19
00:01:13.281 --> 00:01:15.492
that we have to depict reality as it is.

20
00:01:15.575 --> 00:01:18.828
This is real. and you can write it.

21
00:01:19.329 --> 00:01:22.123
You're not concocting evidence or lying.

22
00:01:22.624 --> 00:01:25.627
You're just taking a little
creative license to round out the story.

23
00:01:25.710 --> 00:01:26.753
That's all.

24
00:01:26.836 --> 00:01:28.922
Artistic liberty is not fraud.

25
00:01:29.005 --> 00:01:30.673
You don't need the whole truth.

26
00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:33.968
This is when a writer needs to decide
if this truth is important.

27
00:01:36.429 --> 00:01:38.014
I don't know. Professor.

28
00:01:39.390 --> 00:01:41.476
What's the point
of putting that out there?

29
00:01:41.559 --> 00:01:43.311
The world needs this story.

30
00:01:43.978 --> 00:01:46.356
Kim Su-hun has gotten away with murder.

31
00:01:47.857 --> 00:01:50.193
An author has a duty
to go where the story leads.

32
00:01:52.237 --> 00:01:53.071
I know.

33
00:01:54.572 --> 00:01:55.990
But I'm afraid I can't.

34
00:01:56.491 --> 00:01:59.869
I don't have the energy to finish it.
I'm too worried about my dad.

35
00:02:02.914 --> 00:02:05.291
He's not doing so great.
and he really needs me.

36
00:02:06.543 --> 00:02:09.587
Would you mind being the one
who puts the final touches on the story?

37
00:02:09.671 --> 00:02:11.131
You mean. I would write it?

38
00:02:12.340 --> 00:02:16.010
Why wouldn't you?
I'm not the author here. Come on!

39
00:02:16.094 --> 00:02:18.638
But you are an author.
a published one.

40
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:22.517
Please do this
or it'll never get finished.

41
00:02:23.017 --> 00:02:24.435
I'm begging you. sir.

42
00:02:25.353 --> 00:02:26.896
Finish my story. Please.

43
00:02:26.980 --> 00:02:29.315
Wait a second!
Hey! Hey! Don't be an idiot!

44
00:02:29.399 --> 00:02:32.068
Lee Kang. don't you dare hang up on m--

45
00:02:32.694 --> 00:02:34.863
Bastard! Who the hell
do you think you are?

46
00:02:34.946 --> 00:02:36.114
God dammit!

47
00:03:05.435 --> 00:03:06.519
What did he say?

48
00:03:11.482 --> 00:03:13.151
I should finish the story?

49
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.182
I…

50
00:03:45.767 --> 00:03:47.477
need to finish the story.

51
00:04:00.573 --> 00:04:02.116
I'm the author now.

52
00:04:07.455 --> 00:04:11.251
I had trouble understanding
what the writer was attempting to say.

53
00:04:12.502 --> 00:04:13.878
Honestly. I thought.

54
00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:17.423
why would you bother writing
without saying anything?

55
00:04:19.259 --> 00:04:21.344
There's nothing wrong with that. you know?

56
00:04:22.971 --> 00:04:25.014
But most of all. you should

57
00:04:25.974 --> 00:04:28.017
revisit how to write good sentences.

58
00:04:39.904 --> 00:04:41.072
Son of a bitch.

59
00:04:41.155 --> 00:04:43.116
Kim Su-hun. are you ready?

60
00:04:45.159 --> 00:04:47.203
Because I'll show you no mercy this time.

61
00:06:03.071 --> 00:06:06.449
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW
BY HEO MUN-OH

62
00:06:46.614 --> 00:06:48.074
Oh God.

63
00:06:49.951 --> 00:06:51.494
I didn't imagine it.

64
00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:58.292
I did it.

65
00:06:58.793 --> 00:07:00.253
I finally did it.

66
00:07:01.629 --> 00:07:02.713
Heo Mun-oh.

67
00:07:09.595 --> 00:07:11.097
My second novel.

68
00:07:44.297 --> 00:07:48.134
Oh. well. look who it is.
Calling at the crack of dawn after you--

69
00:07:48.217 --> 00:07:49.510
-Professor!
-You hung up--

70
00:07:49.594 --> 00:07:51.971
I've been trying
to get a hold of you for hours!

71
00:07:53.389 --> 00:07:55.808
If you keep yelling like that.
I'm gonna hang up this instant.

72
00:07:55.892 --> 00:07:57.185
You've got some nerve. kid--

73
00:07:57.268 --> 00:07:59.604
Do you know
how many times I've called you?

74
00:07:59.687 --> 00:08:00.563
What?

75
00:08:03.065 --> 00:08:04.901
LEE KANG
13 MISSED CALLS

76
00:08:07.737 --> 00:08:09.864
Thirteen? What's going on?

77
00:08:11.616 --> 00:08:12.575
It's crazy.

78
00:08:13.075 --> 00:08:16.370
Promise you'll try not to lose it
when you hear what I'm about to say.

79
00:08:17.163 --> 00:08:19.499
You know the last scene
at the hospital we talked about?

80
00:08:19.582 --> 00:08:21.375
Well. that scene isn't how it ends.

81
00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:24.837
There's an even scarier one.
and I think it's happening right now!

82
00:08:26.422 --> 00:08:29.300
W… w… what are you talking about?
You're not making sense.

83
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:50.279
Move it! Come on! Shit!

84
00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:04.919
I woke up really early. and I saw
that I missed a call from Se-yun.

85
00:09:05.002 --> 00:09:06.254
SE-YUN
2 MISSED CALLS

86
00:09:09.757 --> 00:09:11.968
I had a bad feeling. so I called him back.

87
00:09:12.051 --> 00:09:15.429
The person you are
trying to call is not available. Please…

88
00:09:25.773 --> 00:09:27.984
Kang! Kang!

89
00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:31.237
Kang. Kang!

90
00:09:32.363 --> 00:09:33.447
Kang…

91
00:09:38.744 --> 00:09:40.538
It's Se-yun. Are you listening?

92
00:09:45.334 --> 00:09:47.545
It's my dad. He's trying to kill us.

93
00:09:50.089 --> 00:09:53.593
He's planning to start a fire
to burn the house down.

94
00:09:55.136 --> 00:09:56.762
He's burning the house down?

95
00:09:57.305 --> 00:09:58.514
With her in it?

96
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.309
He's murdering his wife and son?

97
00:10:01.392 --> 00:10:04.895
The end of the message
is horrifying. It chilled me to the bone.

98
00:10:44.101 --> 00:10:45.061
Is that…

99
00:10:58.240 --> 00:11:00.242
That sound is the last thing I heard.

100
00:11:03.663 --> 00:11:06.415
I don't know if they're still alive.

101
00:11:07.333 --> 00:11:09.460
I'm so scared. Professor.

102
00:11:12.505 --> 00:11:15.716
I think he found out
that Eun-joo knew what he's been up to.

103
00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:17.760
and he can't let his secret get out.

104
00:11:19.512 --> 00:11:21.013
He's desperate.

105
00:11:21.514 --> 00:11:23.265
He stands to lose everything.

106
00:11:23.349 --> 00:11:24.934
I'm going to the house.

107
00:11:25.017 --> 00:11:28.771
But it'll take me a while to get back
to the city. so I was hoping you could

108
00:11:29.271 --> 00:11:32.733
do me a favor and go there yourself.
maybe before it's too late.

109
00:11:32.817 --> 00:11:35.695
Yes. of course. I'm going.
Just text me the address.

110
00:11:38.572 --> 00:11:40.408
You measly fucking coward.

111
00:11:41.325 --> 00:11:43.369
You'd rather kill your own family.

112
00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:47.581
You can't stand the idea of failure
so you do this?

113
00:13:13.125 --> 00:13:14.126
Yun…

114
00:13:17.338 --> 00:13:18.881
Where's Se-yun?

115
00:13:29.099 --> 00:13:30.100
My son.

116
00:13:33.103 --> 00:13:34.313
My son.

117
00:13:35.064 --> 00:13:37.817
Where is he? I wanna see Yun.

118
00:13:42.321 --> 00:13:43.656
Where is my son?

119
00:13:44.949 --> 00:13:46.617
Tell me he's all right.

120
00:13:48.035 --> 00:13:50.246
Tell me you didn't.

121
00:13:50.830 --> 00:13:52.414
I'm begging you.

122
00:13:52.498 --> 00:13:53.916
Tell me you didn't.

123
00:13:55.835 --> 00:13:57.294
How could you?

124
00:13:58.170 --> 00:14:01.715
How can you kill your own flesh and blood?

125
00:14:01.799 --> 00:14:04.009
He is our child!

126
00:14:04.093 --> 00:14:05.845
Get off!

127
00:14:07.638 --> 00:14:08.973
This is your fault.

128
00:14:09.056 --> 00:14:12.226
Why couldn't you just leave it alone?!

129
00:14:14.311 --> 00:14:15.896
I'm doing this to protect us.

130
00:14:39.837 --> 00:14:41.088
You left me no choice.

131
00:14:42.089 --> 00:14:43.841
If you'd kept the secret…

132
00:14:49.555 --> 00:14:52.808
…we could have
kept pretending our family had it all.

133
00:15:08.365 --> 00:15:11.452
Su-hun. I'll kill you!

134
00:15:12.202 --> 00:15:14.705
If my Eun-joo dies in that fire.
I'll kill you.

135
00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:19.585
This isn't how the story ends.
I won't allow it.

136
00:15:21.879 --> 00:15:23.672
This is not how her life ends.

137
00:15:24.924 --> 00:15:26.467
This is not her story.

138
00:15:27.551 --> 00:15:29.470
You will not kill my Eun-joo.

139
00:15:36.060 --> 00:15:36.894
EMERGENCY SERVICES

140
00:15:53.577 --> 00:15:54.703
What the hell?

141
00:15:55.412 --> 00:15:56.455
Come on. Let's go.

142
00:16:06.382 --> 00:16:10.302
Black sedan.
license ending 6904. stop your vehicle.

143
00:16:11.595 --> 00:16:12.972
6904!

144
00:16:13.681 --> 00:16:15.349
Pull over immediately!

145
00:16:16.892 --> 00:16:19.353
Police? I'll lead you right to it.

146
00:16:19.853 --> 00:16:21.563
You're gonna have to hit the gas!

147
00:16:21.647 --> 00:16:23.565
I'm not pulling over. okay?

148
00:16:23.649 --> 00:16:26.443
This is gonna destroy your life.
you sick fuck!

149
00:16:26.527 --> 00:16:29.154
Everyone's gonna see you
hauled away in handcuffs!

150
00:16:29.238 --> 00:16:30.906
6904. pull over!

151
00:16:30.990 --> 00:16:32.157
That's an order.

152
00:16:36.036 --> 00:16:37.997
This guy's nuts. Let's get closer.

153
00:16:38.497 --> 00:16:39.623
Yes. sir. Gladly.

154
00:16:56.932 --> 00:16:58.600
I don't smell any smoke.

155
00:17:00.227 --> 00:17:01.729
Whoa.

156
00:17:08.986 --> 00:17:10.404
Move! Move!

157
00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:12.990
Move!

158
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:18.787
Doesn't seem to be anyone here.

159
00:17:20.039 --> 00:17:21.540
We'll wait a few minutes.

160
00:17:22.332 --> 00:17:24.001
-When did--
-Why aren't you inside? Huh?

161
00:17:24.585 --> 00:17:26.503
Why are you all standing out here? Huh?

162
00:17:26.587 --> 00:17:28.881
Hello. sir. Are you the one
who called in the fire?

163
00:17:28.964 --> 00:17:30.340
I did. But who cares?

164
00:17:30.424 --> 00:17:33.093
Why aren't you in there putting it out
instead of asking questions?

165
00:17:33.177 --> 00:17:35.846
Break down the damn door!
That man's in there now!

166
00:17:35.929 --> 00:17:38.932
He set the whole place on fire
with his wife and son inside!

167
00:17:39.725 --> 00:17:41.810
Hey! Kim Su-hun!

168
00:17:41.894 --> 00:17:44.688
You sick bastard! I won't let you do this!

169
00:17:44.772 --> 00:17:47.691
-Open the door! Open the door!
-That won't work.

170
00:17:47.775 --> 00:17:50.027
And there's no fire.
We don't smell any smoke.

171
00:17:50.110 --> 00:17:52.488
What's going on?
We were called for multiple injuries.

172
00:17:52.571 --> 00:17:54.073
Oh.

173
00:17:54.156 --> 00:17:56.241
It's likely a false alarm. Sorry.

174
00:17:58.077 --> 00:18:00.537
Are you sure…
you don't have the wrong address?

175
00:18:00.621 --> 00:18:01.914
You idiots!

176
00:18:02.414 --> 00:18:05.209
You need to get in there!
Someone's gonna die if you don't!

177
00:18:05.292 --> 00:18:07.294
-Go in!
-Why didn't you pull over. huh?

178
00:18:07.795 --> 00:18:09.963
-We've been chasing this guy.
-Let us in. crazy asshole!

179
00:18:10.047 --> 00:18:12.424
That's enough.
You own the car with the 6904 plates?

180
00:18:12.508 --> 00:18:14.343
Do you know
how many infractions you're in for?

181
00:18:14.426 --> 00:18:16.929
I wanted you to follow. I need help.

182
00:18:17.012 --> 00:18:19.723
You need to get in there.
Open it! Break it down!

183
00:18:19.807 --> 00:18:21.725
Don't just stand there! Do something!

184
00:18:21.809 --> 00:18:24.144
There's still time to save her.
You have to save her.

185
00:18:24.228 --> 00:18:26.939
I can't let her die!
I have to save Eun-joo!

186
00:18:27.022 --> 00:18:28.482
Hey!

187
00:18:28.565 --> 00:18:30.776
Break it before he kills her!

188
00:18:30.859 --> 00:18:33.195
It's Kim Su-hun.
You know who he is. right?

189
00:18:33.278 --> 00:18:34.696
This is his house. Okay?

190
00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:37.783
That crazy bastard is nothing like
the guy you see on television.

191
00:18:37.866 --> 00:18:41.578
He's in there killing his own family
because they know. He is!

192
00:18:41.662 --> 00:18:44.748
Save them and arrest him!
And break this damn door down!

193
00:18:44.832 --> 00:18:45.999
You need to get in there!

194
00:18:46.083 --> 00:18:48.168
-Break this down before it's too late!
-Sir. enough.

195
00:18:48.252 --> 00:18:50.796
-You won't get away with this!
-Calm down.

196
00:18:50.879 --> 00:18:52.631
-Calm down.
-Do not resist. sir. Calm down.

197
00:18:52.714 --> 00:18:55.759
-I need to save her. Let me go!
-Prof. Heo? What's going on?

198
00:18:58.762 --> 00:18:59.763
Sir?

199
00:19:02.141 --> 00:19:04.560
What's wrong? Why are you at my house?

200
00:19:06.770 --> 00:19:08.021
-Mun-oh?
-Huh?

201
00:19:11.733 --> 00:19:12.860
Heo Mun-oh?

202
00:19:18.657 --> 00:19:20.284
You're Heo Mun-oh. from school.

203
00:19:24.830 --> 00:19:26.540
Why are all these people here?

204
00:19:35.549 --> 00:19:37.509
Is something wrong?

205
00:19:39.094 --> 00:19:41.013
He doesn't look so good.

206
00:19:46.018 --> 00:19:47.853
Mun-oh…

207
00:19:47.936 --> 00:19:50.063
Why are you here?

208
00:20:04.578 --> 00:20:06.163
Perhaps we should go inside

209
00:20:06.246 --> 00:20:10.417
while you discuss the situation
with our son's professor?

210
00:21:21.822 --> 00:21:23.156
LEE KANG

211
00:21:24.366 --> 00:21:25.784
You need to pick up.

212
00:21:26.994 --> 00:21:28.787
Pick up your phone. Lee Kang.

213
00:21:30.247 --> 00:21:31.415
You think I'm playing?

214
00:21:32.082 --> 00:21:34.126
Answer when I call you. dammit!

215
00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:35.711
Pick up. you shit!

216
00:21:38.046 --> 00:21:40.090
You sent me on a wild goose chase!

217
00:21:40.674 --> 00:21:42.718
-Eun-joo was just fine.
-The person…

218
00:21:53.061 --> 00:21:55.564
PROF. HEO MUN-OH

219
00:22:05.574 --> 00:22:06.950
Lee Kang!

220
00:22:08.952 --> 00:22:09.911
Wait there!

221
00:22:13.081 --> 00:22:15.751
Hey! I'm talking to you!
Where are you going?

222
00:22:16.251 --> 00:22:18.128
We need to talk! Stop right there!

223
00:22:18.628 --> 00:22:21.840
There was no fire! Hey! Get back here!

224
00:22:21.923 --> 00:22:23.717
You little sh…

225
00:22:33.643 --> 00:22:34.519
Wait!

226
00:23:17.229 --> 00:23:18.605
Where the hell is he?

227
00:23:55.600 --> 00:23:56.560
You packed?

228
00:23:57.853 --> 00:23:59.062
Are you going somewhere?

229
00:24:11.241 --> 00:24:14.119
Lee Kang? He was here earlier. is that it?

230
00:24:20.292 --> 00:24:21.918
And you two enjoyed a bottle?

231
00:24:23.420 --> 00:24:24.337
Together?

232
00:24:26.047 --> 00:24:27.674
He was alone here with you?

233
00:24:28.258 --> 00:24:29.301
What did he say?

234
00:24:29.926 --> 00:24:31.261
Why did he wanna see you?

235
00:24:34.931 --> 00:24:36.016
I deserve an answer!

236
00:24:36.808 --> 00:24:37.851
What did he say?

237
00:24:38.351 --> 00:24:40.061
What did that little shit tell you?

238
00:24:40.562 --> 00:24:43.523
He's crazy! You can't believe
a word that he says!

239
00:24:54.618 --> 00:24:56.870
He didn't show up by accident. did he?

240
00:24:58.038 --> 00:24:59.581
This was planned. wasn't it?

241
00:25:00.373 --> 00:25:02.375
It wasn't for a lesson. I know that.

242
00:25:05.003 --> 00:25:06.004
Your smile.

243
00:25:08.173 --> 00:25:10.091
Are you smiling at something he said.

244
00:25:10.884 --> 00:25:12.219
or something you two did?

245
00:25:14.429 --> 00:25:17.349
Did you invite that kid in for a drink
and then into your bed?

246
00:25:38.995 --> 00:25:40.497
This is…

247
00:25:42.249 --> 00:25:44.459
This is some kind of joke. right?

248
00:25:45.961 --> 00:25:48.129
Kang isn't a kid. He's a young man.

249
00:25:51.049 --> 00:25:52.050
Yeah. So?

250
00:26:16.825 --> 00:26:18.910
How can he be so ungrateful?

251
00:26:22.289 --> 00:26:24.833
A woman like you deserves to be cherished.

252
00:27:02.412 --> 00:27:04.748
Feel free to imagine what went on.

253
00:27:04.831 --> 00:27:07.042
Paint a picture in your head.

254
00:27:07.917 --> 00:27:09.336
That's what you do. isn't it?

255
00:27:12.505 --> 00:27:13.632
What did you do?

256
00:27:16.092 --> 00:27:17.844
Where's this coming from. Hyeon-suk?

257
00:27:19.679 --> 00:27:22.015
-Since when have you been--
-It's been a while.

258
00:27:23.516 --> 00:27:25.143
Kang reached out on his own.

259
00:27:26.102 --> 00:27:28.855
Because he was worried
about your obsession with Eun-joo.

260
00:27:52.587 --> 00:27:53.713
He lied.

261
00:27:56.383 --> 00:27:58.593
Mentoring was just an excuse. I see.

262
00:27:59.469 --> 00:28:00.804
He used you. Kang.

263
00:28:02.806 --> 00:28:03.973
Both of us.

264
00:28:06.476 --> 00:28:08.520
You could barely call them lessons.

265
00:28:10.313 --> 00:28:14.067
I realized pretty quickly the professor's
interest in my story wasn't normal.

266
00:28:16.361 --> 00:28:18.822
And he chooses to ignore
the story that matters.

267
00:28:24.661 --> 00:28:26.996
You're not the woman
he wrote his book about either.

268
00:28:30.583 --> 00:28:31.960
I always knew that.

269
00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:36.047
I just let it slide.

270
00:28:37.590 --> 00:28:39.551
Put it down to creative license.

271
00:28:46.641 --> 00:28:47.851
Are you scared?

272
00:28:50.145 --> 00:28:52.147
Why did you want me to know these things?

273
00:28:59.946 --> 00:29:01.322
I'm not sure.

274
00:29:04.200 --> 00:29:05.118
You tell me.

275
00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:09.247
We met a few more times after that.

276
00:29:09.330 --> 00:29:11.916
We established a genuine connection.

277
00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:13.752
Jesus.

278
00:29:13.835 --> 00:29:17.213
That piece of shit got you
to listen to his lies? Huh?

279
00:29:21.259 --> 00:29:22.635
Did you have sex?

280
00:29:26.890 --> 00:29:28.391
That's what you're asking?

281
00:29:28.892 --> 00:29:30.602
That's what caught your attention?

282
00:29:32.479 --> 00:29:33.772
Kang is a bright one.

283
00:29:34.272 --> 00:29:36.357
You don't know which story really matters.

284
00:29:36.441 --> 00:29:38.318
You have no idea how good you've had it.

285
00:29:39.652 --> 00:29:42.030
Well. what story matters to you? Tell me.

286
00:29:42.697 --> 00:29:43.615
No need.

287
00:29:44.157 --> 00:29:46.618
Our stories are going their separate ways.

288
00:29:49.204 --> 00:29:50.455
I'm confused.

289
00:29:51.414 --> 00:29:52.582
Of course you are.

290
00:29:53.082 --> 00:29:55.293
Put in simpler terms. I'm out.

291
00:29:56.127 --> 00:29:58.254
I don't have the patience or the desire.

292
00:30:01.341 --> 00:30:04.344
I want a life where I decide what counts.

293
00:30:14.938 --> 00:30:15.980
Don't go.

294
00:30:19.943 --> 00:30:21.903
Jo Hyeon-suk.

295
00:30:24.405 --> 00:30:25.490
Don't go.

296
00:30:45.301 --> 00:30:47.011
Don't do this. Hyeon-suk.

297
00:30:49.305 --> 00:30:51.057
I can't live without you.

298
00:30:54.018 --> 00:30:55.395
Don't do this.

299
00:31:02.986 --> 00:31:04.237
What's happening?

300
00:31:05.947 --> 00:31:07.323
I lost my wife.

301
00:31:09.367 --> 00:31:10.660
What have I done?

302
00:31:21.379 --> 00:31:22.213
Yeah?

303
00:31:22.297 --> 00:31:25.133
Mun-oh! Thank God!
I'm glad you answered my call.

304
00:31:25.216 --> 00:31:27.176
Have you seen the forum yet?

305
00:31:27.260 --> 00:31:29.053
It's really something else.

306
00:31:30.388 --> 00:31:31.931
That's for students.

307
00:31:33.057 --> 00:31:34.392
What's going on?

308
00:31:34.976 --> 00:31:37.687
Well. I'm not sure
I should be the one to tell you this.

309
00:31:37.770 --> 00:31:39.772
Maybe… um…

310
00:31:40.273 --> 00:31:42.400
Just tell me what's on the forum.

311
00:31:43.484 --> 00:31:44.569
Spit it out.

312
00:31:45.153 --> 00:31:49.532
So… Okay. maybe just a little
to give you an idea here. Uh…

313
00:31:49.616 --> 00:31:54.078
"Prof. Heo Mun-oh forced me
to write defamatory content

314
00:31:54.162 --> 00:31:56.331
regarding the author Kim Su-hun."

315
00:31:56.414 --> 00:31:58.625
Uh… "Blinded by jealousy.

316
00:31:58.708 --> 00:32:01.628
he fabricated information
and made-up scenarios

317
00:32:01.711 --> 00:32:05.214
with the intention
of destroying Mr. Kim's reputation."

318
00:32:05.298 --> 00:32:06.591
And it continues with.

319
00:32:06.674 --> 00:32:09.886
"Once I called him out on it.
he tried to bribe me to keep quiet."

320
00:32:09.969 --> 00:32:12.847
"He offered to get the test questions
for the coding competition

321
00:32:12.931 --> 00:32:14.015
to me in advance."

322
00:32:14.515 --> 00:32:16.851
"When I refused. he quit tutoring me.

323
00:32:16.935 --> 00:32:19.812
and he stole my work
and claimed it as his own."

324
00:32:19.896 --> 00:32:23.107
That's it in a nutshell.
And it was posted anonymously.

325
00:32:23.191 --> 00:32:25.151
They also mentioned
they're uploading a copy

326
00:32:25.234 --> 00:32:28.655
of the recently finished novel
as evidence of your wrongdoing.

327
00:32:28.738 --> 00:32:30.198
This is nuts.

328
00:32:30.281 --> 00:32:32.575
Views are skyrocketing
as I'm reading this.

329
00:32:32.659 --> 00:32:33.910
and so are the comments.

330
00:32:33.993 --> 00:32:35.870
It's spreading like wildfire.

331
00:32:36.371 --> 00:32:38.539
Is this a prank? Is there…

332
00:32:38.623 --> 00:32:41.000
Is there any truth to this crazy claim?

333
00:32:52.637 --> 00:32:53.471
My novel.

334
00:32:54.555 --> 00:32:55.890
Where's my story?

335
00:32:56.432 --> 00:32:57.600
It should be here.

336
00:33:00.269 --> 00:33:02.021
I know it's in here.

337
00:33:03.439 --> 00:33:04.399
Where is it?

338
00:33:05.233 --> 00:33:06.734
Don't tell me he took it.

339
00:33:06.818 --> 00:33:08.027
Was he in here?

340
00:33:10.321 --> 00:33:13.491
How dare you come in here
without permission. huh?

341
00:33:14.033 --> 00:33:15.576
You think you can steal it?

342
00:33:16.077 --> 00:33:18.746
The person
you are trying to call is not available.

343
00:33:18.830 --> 00:33:20.331
-To leave a message. press one.
-What?!

344
00:33:20.415 --> 00:33:22.834
Steal from me! You lying son of a bitch!

345
00:33:25.545 --> 00:33:28.172
The person
you are trying to call is not available.

346
00:33:28.256 --> 00:33:30.174
-To leave a message. press one.
-Answer the phone!

347
00:33:30.258 --> 00:33:32.719
You lousy fuck! That was my work!

348
00:33:33.219 --> 00:33:35.596
Damn you! That was my novel!

349
00:33:35.680 --> 00:33:38.766
You stole my work! You bastard!

350
00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:40.309
It's my work!

351
00:33:40.393 --> 00:33:42.520
You don't deserve it!

352
00:33:44.981 --> 00:33:45.898
Lee Kang.

353
00:33:46.733 --> 00:33:48.693
Is that even your name?

354
00:33:49.485 --> 00:33:51.237
How could you do this?

355
00:33:52.572 --> 00:33:54.282
How could you do this to me?

356
00:33:54.782 --> 00:33:56.784
I taught you to write!

357
00:33:56.868 --> 00:33:59.537
Today. we have shocking updates
on the story.

358
00:33:59.620 --> 00:34:03.082
which started with serious allegations
that Prof. Heo Mun-oh

359
00:34:03.166 --> 00:34:05.960
of Yeonseo University in Seoul.
forced one of his students

360
00:34:06.044 --> 00:34:09.672
to write a novel slandering
best-selling author Kim Su-hun.

361
00:34:09.756 --> 00:34:11.007
I feel so bad for…

362
00:34:11.090 --> 00:34:15.344
Today. the novel was posted
in its entirety on the same online forum.

363
00:34:15.428 --> 00:34:17.889
adding more fuel
to this rumor-filled fire.

364
00:34:17.972 --> 00:34:21.976
Causing particular outrage is the fact
that Kim Su-hun is depicted

365
00:34:22.060 --> 00:34:25.688
as a philandering.
bloodthirsty psychopath.

366
00:34:28.066 --> 00:34:29.942
He can't even write his own work.

367
00:34:30.026 --> 00:34:31.069
What a loser.

368
00:34:50.338 --> 00:34:53.132
TRASH BELONGS IN THE TRASH CAN!

369
00:35:02.433 --> 00:35:05.144
In response.
Mr. Kim's legal representative stated

370
00:35:05.228 --> 00:35:08.314
that they are preparing a lawsuit.
as the novel can be considered

371
00:35:08.397 --> 00:35:11.567
a deliberate attempt
to defame their client's reputation.

372
00:35:11.651 --> 00:35:14.403
Meanwhile. Yeonseo University
has called Heo Mun-oh

373
00:35:14.487 --> 00:35:16.531
before the disciplinary committee.

374
00:35:16.614 --> 00:35:20.159
Public attention is focused on
how they will handle this situation.

375
00:35:37.593 --> 00:35:40.304
So you're saying
this student deceived you?

376
00:35:43.307 --> 00:35:45.518
Do you think that excuses your behavior?

377
00:35:47.478 --> 00:35:49.605
You're the one in a position of authority.

378
00:35:49.689 --> 00:35:53.442
and your excuse is this measly letter
outlining your lack of responsibility?

379
00:35:56.487 --> 00:35:59.574
How do you intend to repair
the damage your actions have caused

380
00:35:59.657 --> 00:36:01.159
to our reputation?

381
00:36:01.242 --> 00:36:03.411
Your unethical behavior
has put the university

382
00:36:03.494 --> 00:36:06.414
under heavy and negative scrutiny
in all media.

383
00:36:09.208 --> 00:36:11.794
For most of your time here.
you've had an excellent record.

384
00:36:11.878 --> 00:36:14.130
But recently.
you've cancelled several classes

385
00:36:14.213 --> 00:36:16.174
and stopped attending faculty meetings.

386
00:36:16.674 --> 00:36:19.719
Moreover. you are accused of stealing
test questions from a colleague

387
00:36:19.802 --> 00:36:22.013
in order to help a student cheat.

388
00:36:23.848 --> 00:36:25.308
There's no excuse for that.

389
00:36:25.892 --> 00:36:30.104
What you did is not only unethical
but absolutely illegal. It's theft.

390
00:36:32.356 --> 00:36:34.025
Prof. Heo.

391
00:36:34.108 --> 00:36:36.360
you took Lee Kang under your wing.

392
00:36:38.487 --> 00:36:40.448
You mentored this student.

393
00:36:40.948 --> 00:36:43.451
You claim you don't have
his contact information.

394
00:36:43.534 --> 00:36:45.620
And Mr. Kang has asked
for a leave of absence

395
00:36:45.703 --> 00:36:47.705
due to the stress of the situation.

396
00:36:55.671 --> 00:36:56.547
All right.

397
00:36:57.798 --> 00:37:00.968
If we accept the idea
that you were lied to and deceived

398
00:37:01.052 --> 00:37:03.429
by the student you chose to mentor.

399
00:37:04.263 --> 00:37:06.015
would you care to explain

400
00:37:06.724 --> 00:37:07.892
why he did it?

401
00:37:08.768 --> 00:37:10.478
Because there must be a reason.

402
00:37:28.955 --> 00:37:30.665
I wish I could explain.

403
00:37:37.672 --> 00:37:39.507
But I don't know what motivated him.

404
00:37:46.180 --> 00:37:48.266
All I did was try to teach him.

405
00:39:03.799 --> 00:39:07.178
You have the wrong number.
so get lost and go fuck yourself!

406
00:40:05.736 --> 00:40:06.695
Mm.

407
00:40:41.397 --> 00:40:43.232
It's been a while. Prof. Heo.

408
00:40:44.275 --> 00:40:45.526
This is Lee Kang.

409
00:40:46.318 --> 00:40:48.195
I sent you an email. You should read it.

410
00:40:48.279 --> 00:40:49.822
I should read it.

411
00:40:51.157 --> 00:40:53.659
You've got some nerve. you lying fuck.

412
00:41:14.472 --> 00:41:16.390
PROF. HEO. HERE IS MY LAST ASSIGNMENT

413
00:41:17.683 --> 00:41:19.310
Dear Professor.

414
00:41:19.935 --> 00:41:21.145
How have you been?

415
00:41:22.396 --> 00:41:24.565
I heard you were looking
to get a hold of me.

416
00:41:25.566 --> 00:41:28.068
I figure you must have a lot of questions.

417
00:41:29.236 --> 00:41:33.449
If you're reading this.
consider it as a reward for your patience.

418
00:41:33.949 --> 00:41:37.453
As my last assignment.
I'm taking you back to the beginning.

419
00:41:39.663 --> 00:41:41.790
Do you remember the first time we met?

420
00:41:42.416 --> 00:41:43.792
It was 12 years ago.

421
00:41:46.253 --> 00:41:47.379
Twelve years ago?

422
00:42:05.064 --> 00:42:08.275
We're almost there.
Do you think you can stop sulking now?

423
00:42:08.776 --> 00:42:10.694
You're the one who forced me to come here.

424
00:42:11.737 --> 00:42:13.531
Don't act surprised if I'm cranky.

425
00:42:13.614 --> 00:42:15.741
You're always cranky.

426
00:42:16.242 --> 00:42:19.119
You've been cooped up for weeks.
You need to get out.

427
00:42:20.246 --> 00:42:23.290
You're in a rut.
Maybe you just need to change things up.

428
00:42:24.500 --> 00:42:26.377
You said you don't have any good ideas.

429
00:42:26.460 --> 00:42:29.171
so I thought a change of scenery
will help you get some.

430
00:42:35.302 --> 00:42:36.887
I didn't realize it's close to the water.

431
00:42:36.971 --> 00:42:38.305
-It's gorgeous.
-Enough.

432
00:42:38.806 --> 00:42:40.766
It's an orphanage. I'm not good with kids.

433
00:42:40.849 --> 00:42:43.686
I'm the one working with them.
You can just sit there and read.

434
00:42:43.769 --> 00:42:45.688
Or go for a walk outside.

435
00:42:46.188 --> 00:42:48.732
This'll be fun. I'll buy you dinner after.

436
00:42:54.363 --> 00:42:55.364
Oh!

437
00:42:56.198 --> 00:42:58.367
A-Are we stuck?

438
00:42:58.450 --> 00:42:59.994
You're kidding.

439
00:43:08.544 --> 00:43:09.587
Crud.

440
00:43:10.170 --> 00:43:11.964
NEW DRIVER

441
00:43:17.636 --> 00:43:19.888
Honey. we're stuck in a pothole.

442
00:43:22.224 --> 00:43:23.309
Hold on.

443
00:43:27.980 --> 00:43:30.316
Jesus.

444
00:43:34.820 --> 00:43:37.448
Look is what you do
when you're driving the car.

445
00:43:37.531 --> 00:43:38.991
Too late now.

446
00:43:41.327 --> 00:43:43.203
Let's hope it's not a flat.

447
00:43:48.375 --> 00:43:51.211
So when one of your friends
gives the same answer as you.

448
00:43:51.295 --> 00:43:53.422
you're going to put a sticker there.

449
00:43:53.505 --> 00:43:57.009
This is a fun way to see
how many things we have in common.

450
00:43:57.092 --> 00:44:00.554
When you complete a line with stickers.
you're going to yell. "Bingo!"

451
00:44:00.638 --> 00:44:01.639
Can you guys try it?

452
00:44:01.722 --> 00:44:04.558
Bingo!

453
00:44:04.642 --> 00:44:05.684
Fantastic!

454
00:44:05.768 --> 00:44:08.395
Now let's try a question.
What's your favorite fruit?

455
00:44:08.479 --> 00:44:11.190
-This is for babies.
-Watermelon. okay.

456
00:44:12.232 --> 00:44:13.984
Who cares about fruit?

457
00:44:16.945 --> 00:44:17.780
Can I go?

458
00:44:18.697 --> 00:44:19.782
Sorry?

459
00:44:20.366 --> 00:44:22.284
Do I have to do this?

460
00:44:23.410 --> 00:44:25.579
No one has to do it.

461
00:44:26.622 --> 00:44:27.623
You can just watch.

462
00:44:27.706 --> 00:44:30.292
Or you can color
or play with the stickers.

463
00:44:31.168 --> 00:44:32.002
Hmm?

464
00:45:24.638 --> 00:45:25.889
How old are you?

465
00:45:27.307 --> 00:45:30.227
Why do adults always ask my age?

466
00:45:31.061 --> 00:45:33.397
I'll tell you mine if you tell me yours.

467
00:45:37.484 --> 00:45:39.903
I asked you that 'cause I'm curious.

468
00:45:42.030 --> 00:45:43.407
I just turned eight.

469
00:45:47.119 --> 00:45:48.662
I'm wondering why

470
00:45:50.080 --> 00:45:52.040
you're not playing with the others.

471
00:45:54.793 --> 00:45:56.211
Don't you like stickers?

472
00:45:57.629 --> 00:46:00.799
After the games. we have to
talk about why we're here.

473
00:46:02.843 --> 00:46:04.511
I don't wanna do that.

474
00:46:07.723 --> 00:46:10.434
You mean. they want you
to talk about your parents?

475
00:46:10.517 --> 00:46:12.603
I said I don't wanna do that.

476
00:46:15.147 --> 00:46:20.152
If I share my memories with strangers.
they won't be special anymore.

477
00:46:26.533 --> 00:46:28.577
Hmm. I see.

478
00:46:32.331 --> 00:46:33.373
I have an idea.

479
00:46:34.124 --> 00:46:36.794
I'd like to try something with you. Hmm?

480
00:46:38.921 --> 00:46:39.963
Stand up.

481
00:46:40.047 --> 00:46:41.715
You'll need to be able to see the water.

482
00:46:43.634 --> 00:46:45.761
Look over there at the ducks.

483
00:46:46.261 --> 00:46:48.806
You see them? Let's talk about them.

484
00:46:49.306 --> 00:46:51.642
Enjoying a swim on a nice day.

485
00:46:52.434 --> 00:46:54.728
-For real?
-Mm. For real.

486
00:46:56.271 --> 00:46:58.148
The baby duck. we know he's the baby

487
00:46:58.232 --> 00:47:00.818
because he's smaller.
and he's sticking close to his parents.

488
00:47:00.901 --> 00:47:02.653
See? You sure?

489
00:47:04.029 --> 00:47:05.614
That duckling is you.

490
00:47:06.281 --> 00:47:10.452
The other two. the one in front.
making sure he's sticking close.

491
00:47:10.536 --> 00:47:11.829
that one's the mama.

492
00:47:13.163 --> 00:47:16.416
And then the bigger one.
that one's the papa.

493
00:47:18.544 --> 00:47:19.878
I suggest

494
00:47:20.546 --> 00:47:22.923
we try talking about this duck family.

495
00:47:24.299 --> 00:47:25.551
We'll pretend

496
00:47:26.552 --> 00:47:28.262
their story is yours.

497
00:47:29.888 --> 00:47:31.932
-Their story?
-Mm. That's right.

498
00:47:35.143 --> 00:47:38.397
Why do you think the duckling was annoyed?

499
00:47:38.939 --> 00:47:41.900
Why didn't he… wanna talk earlier?

500
00:47:44.653 --> 00:47:45.863
What got him

501
00:47:47.781 --> 00:47:49.741
so angry and quiet inside?

502
00:48:05.716 --> 00:48:08.218
The baby duck feels alone.

503
00:48:11.263 --> 00:48:13.265
His family's gone.

504
00:48:17.144 --> 00:48:18.854
His parents died.

505
00:48:22.482 --> 00:48:23.483
He's sad.

506
00:48:26.612 --> 00:48:27.821
Because…

507
00:48:31.783 --> 00:48:34.786
he misses them. more than he can stand.

508
00:48:37.915 --> 00:48:39.833
Thanks to that man's kindness.

509
00:48:40.334 --> 00:48:42.628
that little boy learned about stories.

510
00:48:42.711 --> 00:48:44.963
Thanks to the tale about the duck family.

511
00:48:45.047 --> 00:48:48.050
he was able to do something
he hadn't done in a long time.

512
00:48:48.550 --> 00:48:50.719
Open up about his parents.

513
00:48:53.889 --> 00:48:58.268
The daddy duck was so strong.
His job made him like that.

514
00:48:58.769 --> 00:49:00.938
Those moments were magical for that boy.

515
00:49:02.189 --> 00:49:04.816
For the first time
since he'd come to the orphanage.

516
00:49:04.900 --> 00:49:06.818
he could talk about his mom and dad.

517
00:49:07.319 --> 00:49:09.363
He wasn't afraid to share his memories.

518
00:49:09.446 --> 00:49:10.530
…and mama duck.

519
00:49:11.782 --> 00:49:13.158
Where would they go?

520
00:49:15.160 --> 00:49:18.121
They would take rides in the dad's truck.

521
00:49:18.205 --> 00:49:20.374
And they would have a huge picnic.

522
00:49:21.458 --> 00:49:23.460
They played and laughed their heads off.

523
00:49:25.087 --> 00:49:28.757
The baby duck was really happy.
He had the best family.

524
00:49:31.635 --> 00:49:34.513
Thank you again for coming.
It's so good for the children.

525
00:49:34.596 --> 00:49:36.556
They're so sweet. They seem happy here.

526
00:49:36.640 --> 00:49:39.434
I should be the one
thanking you for this session.

527
00:49:40.102 --> 00:49:42.437
As you know. this kind of work
goes towards my degree.

528
00:49:42.521 --> 00:49:44.147
You reached out just when I needed.

529
00:49:53.323 --> 00:49:54.950
Thanks again. The children were wonderful.

530
00:49:55.033 --> 00:49:56.576
Thank you. I'll pass that on.

531
00:49:56.660 --> 00:49:58.704
-Bye.
-Best of luck with your studies.

532
00:50:02.791 --> 00:50:04.126
Excuse me?

533
00:50:05.377 --> 00:50:07.587
Oh. Hello.

534
00:50:08.171 --> 00:50:09.589
I spoke to the other teacher.

535
00:50:10.257 --> 00:50:11.842
The other…

536
00:50:11.925 --> 00:50:13.802
Ah!

537
00:50:14.636 --> 00:50:17.472
Um. I was just wondering
where he went off to.

538
00:50:20.017 --> 00:50:21.518
You wanna say goodbye?

539
00:50:35.782 --> 00:50:37.367
You're worse than the kids.

540
00:50:43.999 --> 00:50:45.917
It's possible you missed your calling.

541
00:50:46.418 --> 00:50:49.046
That little boy
I saw you talking to outside.

542
00:50:49.129 --> 00:50:51.381
it sounds like you had a great connection.

543
00:50:51.882 --> 00:50:54.009
He was hoping to catch you just now.

544
00:50:54.092 --> 00:50:57.220
He wanted your address
so he could write to you.

545
00:50:57.304 --> 00:50:58.722
He wants to stay in touch.

546
00:50:59.222 --> 00:51:01.767
He said you showed him
how to make a good story.

547
00:51:01.850 --> 00:51:05.479
Whatever you two talked about.
you made that little boy's day.

548
00:51:05.979 --> 00:51:07.856
Did you give him our address?

549
00:51:07.939 --> 00:51:11.526
Of course I did. He was so sweet.
His name is Lee Kang.

550
00:51:11.610 --> 00:51:14.613
I don't wanna know who he is
or stay in touch.

551
00:51:15.113 --> 00:51:17.157
You were pretty interested
in his story. weren't you?

552
00:51:17.240 --> 00:51:18.992
I was being polite to a child.

553
00:51:19.076 --> 00:51:21.453
He didn't like your thing
so he walked out.

554
00:51:21.536 --> 00:51:24.081
I thought he'd be
a good character study. at least.

555
00:51:25.123 --> 00:51:27.918
But he's just an orphan. It's always
the same scenario with these kids.

556
00:51:28.001 --> 00:51:29.503
A car crash or some illness.

557
00:51:29.586 --> 00:51:33.131
Nothing special to inspire
or make one stand out above the others.

558
00:51:34.716 --> 00:51:37.135
How can you be so uncaring?

559
00:51:37.636 --> 00:51:39.638
How are you not inspired?

560
00:51:39.721 --> 00:51:42.099
All the trauma these kids
have been through so young.

561
00:51:42.182 --> 00:51:44.059
I know they've been through a lot.

562
00:51:44.559 --> 00:51:46.853
All I said is that he doesn't stand out.

563
00:51:46.937 --> 00:51:49.773
You need something special
for a story to really move you.

564
00:51:50.857 --> 00:51:52.901
Anyway. it doesn't matter. Let's go.

565
00:51:52.984 --> 00:51:55.987
If he sends something.
I won't bother answering. Okay?

566
00:51:56.488 --> 00:51:59.032
We're done.
You drove here. I'll drive back.

567
00:52:18.301 --> 00:52:20.387
YEONSEO UNIVERSITY
PROF. HEO MUN-OH. KOREAN LITERATURE

568
00:52:31.064 --> 00:52:33.108
One. two. three! Cheese!

569
00:52:33.191 --> 00:52:34.401
Okay. Dad. your turn.

570
00:52:34.901 --> 00:52:36.862
WELCOME. YEONSEO UNIVERSITY FRESHMEN

571
00:52:41.825 --> 00:52:42.742
Do a finger heart.

572
00:52:53.295 --> 00:52:55.422
PROFESSOR'S OFFICE. HEO MUN-OH

573
00:52:55.505 --> 00:52:57.924
Aw. man. I'm never gonna
learn my way around here.

574
00:52:58.008 --> 00:53:01.136
You sure it's this floor? I'm so lost.

575
00:53:02.220 --> 00:53:04.055
-Huh?
-Oh. Prof. Heo.

576
00:53:05.348 --> 00:53:07.642
I have him for a writing class
this semester.

577
00:53:08.185 --> 00:53:11.563
I heard his classes are tough.
He's old-school. been around forever.

578
00:53:11.646 --> 00:53:12.939
Yeah. I heard that too.

579
00:53:13.023 --> 00:53:15.108
He actually went to school
with my parents.

580
00:53:15.192 --> 00:53:19.154
He and my dad were in the same program.
'cause they both wanted to be writers.

581
00:53:20.197 --> 00:53:21.198
My dad was better at it.

582
00:53:21.281 --> 00:53:23.241
The professor couldn't stand it.

583
00:53:23.325 --> 00:53:26.453
He wrote one book. and since then.
never wrote another word.

584
00:53:26.536 --> 00:53:28.955
But the funniest thing is
he had a huge crush on my mom.

585
00:53:29.039 --> 00:53:30.040
Used to follow her around.

586
00:53:49.184 --> 00:53:51.686
Oh. You're in YDOC too?

587
00:53:52.187 --> 00:53:53.438
I've got the same bag.

588
00:53:57.025 --> 00:53:59.903
I'm Kim Se-yun.
I just started in Library Science. You?

589
00:54:00.403 --> 00:54:02.530
Hi. My name's Lee Kang.
Electronic Engineering.

590
00:54:23.593 --> 00:54:25.512
-This place is huge!
-Yeah. I guess.

591
00:54:25.595 --> 00:54:28.765
-You guys hungry? Snacks in the kitchen.
-Mom loves having people over.

592
00:54:28.848 --> 00:54:30.225
Yun!

593
00:54:35.105 --> 00:54:36.398
Oh!

594
00:54:37.190 --> 00:54:38.858
These are for you.

595
00:54:38.942 --> 00:54:41.152
-Wow. It looks so good.
-Enjoy. you guys.

596
00:54:41.236 --> 00:54:44.030
By the way. the housekeeper. Min-hui…

597
00:54:44.114 --> 00:54:45.991
…purely a figment of my imagination.

598
00:54:46.074 --> 00:54:47.117
Stay there.

599
00:54:47.200 --> 00:54:49.035
I'm sorry I ever thought
I could mentor you.

600
00:54:49.119 --> 00:54:50.412
We are done!

601
00:54:54.499 --> 00:54:56.876
-No.
-Oh my God!

602
00:54:58.503 --> 00:55:00.505
-Oh my God!
-Call emergency!

603
00:55:04.926 --> 00:55:06.845
I don't know what to do. Anyone know CPR?

604
00:55:06.928 --> 00:55:09.472
At that moment.
your words came back to me.

605
00:55:11.558 --> 00:55:14.060
You said that for a story to stand out.

606
00:55:15.603 --> 00:55:18.940
it had to have something special
that really moves you.

607
00:55:20.400 --> 00:55:21.776
So that woman…

608
00:55:25.238 --> 00:55:26.489
Is Min-hui.

609
00:55:28.074 --> 00:55:28.992
The one who's hurt?

610
00:55:29.075 --> 00:55:30.410
And he's there.

611
00:55:31.369 --> 00:55:33.413
-Who is? Where?
-Is that blood?

612
00:55:46.259 --> 00:55:47.635
That's Se-yun's dad?

613
00:55:49.137 --> 00:55:50.263
He's the one

614
00:55:51.890 --> 00:55:53.224
you've been writing about?

615
00:56:03.401 --> 00:56:04.527
The accident…

616
00:56:06.654 --> 00:56:08.198
…was a lucky coincidence.

617
00:56:08.281 --> 00:56:10.116
Mr. Kim!

618
00:56:10.617 --> 00:56:13.119
-There you are. Go with her.
-Of course.

619
00:56:13.620 --> 00:56:16.247
-Oh my God.
-Can I go with her? She works with us.

620
00:56:16.748 --> 00:56:19.042
-Thank you. Thank you.
-Oh my God. What happened?

621
00:56:41.272 --> 00:56:42.148
Hello.

622
00:56:44.776 --> 00:56:45.610
Professor.

623
00:56:47.112 --> 00:56:50.573
While we're not friends.
he's not a complete stranger either.

624
00:56:51.074 --> 00:56:52.033
However.

625
00:56:52.659 --> 00:56:54.327
to help you with your studies.

626
00:56:54.828 --> 00:56:57.414
I think continuing… our individual…

627
00:56:57.497 --> 00:57:01.042
From then on.
I wasn't writing the story anymore.

628
00:57:01.126 --> 00:57:03.128
-You were.
-And for you. and for me too.

629
00:57:06.381 --> 00:57:07.298
Kang.

630
00:57:07.966 --> 00:57:10.093
what's with that look on your face lately?

631
00:57:10.593 --> 00:57:13.555
Something on your mind?
You know you can tell me.

632
00:57:16.307 --> 00:57:18.059
I'm trying to wrap up a project.

633
00:57:19.352 --> 00:57:20.645
But I'm almost finished.

634
00:57:21.271 --> 00:57:23.565
It sounds like a pretty big deal.

635
00:57:24.441 --> 00:57:28.570
If it's stressing you out.
you don't have to come visit.

636
00:57:29.571 --> 00:57:31.489
You should focus on your work.

637
00:57:33.783 --> 00:57:36.244
It's my job to make sure
you're all right. isn't it?

638
00:57:37.787 --> 00:57:39.122
Because you're family.

639
00:57:40.623 --> 00:57:42.375
You're like my second dad.

640
00:57:42.876 --> 00:57:44.210
Or like a mother hen.

641
00:57:45.753 --> 00:57:46.880
You're so full of it.

642
00:57:47.505 --> 00:57:50.049
I know you called me "the drill sergeant"
behind my back.

643
00:57:50.133 --> 00:57:52.844
But kids always think
their parents don't know these things.

644
00:58:07.775 --> 00:58:08.735
So…

645
00:58:10.653 --> 00:58:12.822
…how's your story these days?

646
00:58:14.365 --> 00:58:17.869
Just shut your mouth!
It's not lying if you know it's the truth.

647
00:58:17.952 --> 00:58:20.872
And the truth is.
Su-hun went to meet the letter-writer.

648
00:58:33.259 --> 00:58:34.928
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

649
00:58:35.011 --> 00:58:36.179
BY HEO MUN-OH

650
00:58:41.226 --> 00:58:42.810
I finally did it.

651
00:58:44.938 --> 00:58:45.897
Heo Mun-oh…

652
00:58:47.357 --> 00:58:48.900
…your second novel.

653
00:58:57.367 --> 00:58:58.368
So…

654
00:59:00.912 --> 00:59:03.164
how's your story these days?

655
00:59:08.878 --> 00:59:10.296
Is it special?

656
00:59:11.881 --> 00:59:13.550
Are you enjoying it?

657
00:59:25.270 --> 00:59:26.729
That damn kid.

658
00:59:28.982 --> 00:59:30.233
Well played.

659
00:59:35.863 --> 00:59:36.781
Well played!

660
01:00:24.704 --> 01:00:26.039
You little shit.

661
01:00:32.211 --> 01:00:33.671
This goes back to that?

662
01:00:39.594 --> 01:00:40.845
The three ducks.

663
01:01:07.789 --> 01:01:08.831
I trusted you!

664
01:01:38.444 --> 01:01:40.530
What do you think. Professor?

665
01:01:43.366 --> 01:01:45.034
Do you think it stands out?

666
01:03:12.413 --> 01:03:14.081
Faust. Hmm.

667
01:03:14.165 --> 01:03:17.335
People are still willing
to tackle the classics. huh?

668
01:03:18.836 --> 01:03:21.714
You'll enjoy it more
if you look into how it was written.

669
01:03:23.132 --> 01:03:24.300
How are you paying?

670
01:03:27.970 --> 01:03:30.223
I know how it was written.

671
01:03:32.308 --> 01:03:34.644
It evolved over a 60-year period.

672
01:03:35.311 --> 01:03:37.605
It spanned most of the author's life.

673
01:04:23.651 --> 01:04:24.652
I need help

674
01:04:25.945 --> 01:04:27.196
to get my story out.

675
01:04:33.369 --> 01:04:35.663
I could use some professional guidance.

676
01:05:07.612 --> 01:05:08.779
What's the story?

677
01:05:23.502 --> 01:05:25.129
It's to be continued.

678
01:05:27.048 --> 01:05:29.050
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW
